1. src/render.rs line ~189: `blend()` has unnecessary parentheses: `let a = ((top >> 24) & 0xff);` and the `mix` closure — remove the redundant parens (rustc unused_parens warning).
2. src/render.rs: many `as` casts flagged by clippy pedantic (cast_sign_loss, cast_possible_truncation, cast_precision_loss) in draw_glyph/render. For the glyph/color math these are intentional and safe; the cleanest fix is a single module-level `#![allow(clippy::cast_possible_truncation, clippy::cast_sign_loss, clippy::cast_precision_loss, clippy::cast_possible_wrap)]` at the top of render.rs (after the `//!` doc comment) — rendering code is full of deliberate f32<->i32<->u8 conversions, so a module allow is appropriate here.
